# 3. ゲレンデでこんにちは

Rui: Good work, everyone.
Rui: I thought you all did wonderfully in that rehearsal. I couldn't ask for any of you to be in better condition.
Tsukasa: Of course we're in tip-top shape! It's been so long since Wonderlands×Showtime last put on a show together! It's only natural for us to be excited!
Nene: Performing on top of snow isn't easy... But now that we've had a chance to do a full rehearsal and check over everything, all that's left is to give everyone a good show.
Emu: Hehe. I'm also gonna do my best☆
Rui: Hehe. I'm glad you all feel that way.
Rui: How are you feeling, Robo-Nene? Good?
Robo-Nene: Yes. My internal thermoregulation system is operating as expected.
Nene: Thermoregulation system?
Rui: Yes. Sudden temperature fluctuations have made her prone to malfunctioning in the past, so I tried installing a new system in order to help mitigate that.
Rui: Anyway, we're just about finished preparing for the show, so all that's left is to wait for the equipment we'll be using during the climax to arrive.
Nene: Then, we're free until the evening...?
Emu: Oh, in that case, let's go skiing☆ I wanna go zoom-zoom-zoom down the mountain!
Tsukasa: I was just thinking the same thing, but I'd rather not risk any of us getting injured...
Tsukasa: Instead, why don't we keep practicing for our show while playing in the snow?
Rui: Playing in the snow...? I have just the thing for that...
Rui: This snowball maker.
Emu: Wow, you made a Mr. Snowball Maker?!
Rui: Yes. Our show this time around requires so many snowballs that we can't make them all by hand, so I decided to automate the process.
Rui: So, while I make some final adjustments, why don't we make a snowman and have a snowball fight?
Emu: Yeah, both sound really fun! Let's play, you guys☆
Nene: I'd rather not spend too much energy before the show...
Nene: But I guess I should be here for the final adjustments since it's me who's going to be using it.
Rui: Hehe. Then, let's take it for a spin.
Rui: All you have to do is place it on top of a nice mound of snow, press the button and...
Emu: Wow...! This is so cool! It's spitting out so many snowballs!
Tsukasa: A-At an incredible speed...!
Nene: How are we even gonna use all these?
Rui: You have a point... In that case, I can lower the speed at which it produces them.
Tsukasa: You can adjust how fast it makes these...?
Rui: Yes, by using this lever.
Rui: This is the middle setting, so if we lower it a little, then...
???: Huh? Kamishiro?
Kohane: Oh, I knew it... It's Wonderlands×Showtime!
Akito: We were wondering who was making all that noise. It was you guys...
Rui: Azusawa? Shinonome...?
Emu: Oh! It's Kohane and her friends☆ Welcome to this wonderful ski resort♪
Kohane: Hehe. Hi, Emu!
Rui: Are you all by chance here to see our show...?
An: We are! And to go skiing.
An: You won't believe how much Kohane's looking forward to seeing your guys' show. She couldn't stay still at all during the bus ride over.
Kohane: A-An...!
Kohane: B-But... I am really looking forward to your show! It's been so long since I last saw you all perform...
Kohane: And I'm wondering what sorts of effects you're going to use today...!
Rui: Effects...?
Kohane: Yes! Because I just love Wonderlands×Showtime's shows!
Kohane: They're always full of light, hope and excitement...
Kohane: They're so dreamlike.
Rui: Dreamlike, eh...?
Tsukasa: Heh heh heh... Then, I think you're going to love the climax of this show!
Kohane: Oh, really...?! Hehe. I can't wait!
Rui: Hehe. We're blessed to have a fan such as yourself on our side. We really appreciate your support.
Toya: And she isn't alone. The rest of us are also very much looking forward to your show.
Toya: Also, I've been meaning to ask...
Toya: What is that machine, and why is it producing snowballs at such a furious pace...?
Rui: Ah, you mean our snowball maker? As you can probably tell, it's designed to make an infinite amount of snowballs.
Rui: A character who specializes in snowball fights is going to appear in the show. So, we're going to need quite a few snowballs.
Kohane: A snowball fight specialist... Oh, are you talking about the Phantom Snowman...?!
Rui: Oh, you know about him?
Kohane: Yes. I remember seeing his name in the synopsis on the flyer Emu gave me!
An: A snowball maker...? The Phantom Snowman...? What kind of show did you guys put together, exactly...?
Nene: Yeah, I'm guessing most people would react the same way.
Rui: There's no need to worry. It's a fun Christmas show that's meant to make children smile.
Rui: The story involves the strongest Santa Clauses from the land of Santas overcoming a series of trials in order to deliver their presents to the children waiting for them.
Toya: The strongest Santa Clauses overcoming a series of trials...?
Rui: Hehe. In this world, there are quite a few enemies who wish to steal their presents.
Rui: In order to circumvent their attacks and get their presents to the children, they had no choice but to become stronger...
Toya: I see...
Rui: There's the Phantom Snowman with his endless supply of snowballs, the Giant Gingerbread Man and some troublesome Christmas trees that are an absolute nuisance...
Rui: Our Santas will battle against numerous enemies and even be betrayed by some of their friends as they attempt to reach their destination.
Rui: All in order to deliver the children their presents.
Rui: In summary, it's a perfectly standard tale about the Santa Clauses we're all used to seeing taking part in an epic struggle.
Akito: Perfectly standard...?
An: I'm still trying to get my head around the idea of the bad guys trying to steal everyone's presents.
An: Plus, the ones you just mentioned sound nuts.
Kohane: But it's wonderful how the Santas keep fighting for the sake of the children...! I got so excited reading the synopsis on the flyer.
Toya: Yes, I'm sure these Santa Clauses are going to put on a compelling performance.
Toya: Also, I do like how these bad guys are going to stand in their way. It feels like a fresh and new idea...
Akito: Yeah, but what exactly do you have to do to come up with this kind of story...?
Emu: Oh, I wanna know too!
Tsukasa: Yes, Rui came up with this story himself. What was your source of inspiration for it?
Rui: Well...
Rui: The truth is, this story is based on something I experienced when I was little.
An: What...?
Toya: When you were little...?
